  "prompt": "What is the formula to calculate a synchronous speed of a motor?",
  "response": "The synchronous speed of an AC motor is determined by the formula:\n\n\\[ n_s = \\frac{120 \\times f}{P} \\]\n\nWhere:\n- \\( n_s \\) is the synchronous speed in revolutions per minute (RPM).\n- \\( f \\) is the frequency of the AC power supply in hertz (Hz).\n- \\( P \\) is the number of poles of the motor.\n\nThis formula shows that the synchronous speed is directly proportional to the frequency of the AC supply and inversely proportional to the number of poles in the motor.",
